obo:RO_0002333  a  owl:ObjectProperty .

gomodel:SYNGO_4883  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 1a: experimental design; to determine the specificities of G-protein Gβγ subunits for the SNARE complex upon activation of α2a-Adrenergic Receptor (ADRA2A), authors used synaptosomes collected from the brains of wild-type, α2aAR KO, and FLAG-α2a-Adrenergic Receptor mice and co-IP of SNAP25 and Gβγ.\n\nFigure 3, 7: anti-SNAP25 pulldown yields Gγ4 (GNG4) and the relative amount thereof was affected by epinephrine stimulation to activate the α2a-Adrenergic Receptor.. Experimental description: result section: \"To determine the specificities of Gβγ subunits for the SNARE complex upon activation of α2aAR, we used synaptosomes collected from the brains of wild-type (WT), α2aAR KO, and FLAG-α2aAR mice.\"\n\nM&M:\n\"Epinephrine (catalog E4642), prazosin (catalog P7791), and propranolol (catalog P0884) were purchased from Sigma-Aldrich.\"\n\n\"For immunoprecipitations, rabbit anti-SNAP25 (Sigma-Aldrich, S9684) and rabbit ChromePure IgG (Jackson Immunoresearch, 011-030-003) were used.\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2022-09-11" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4883" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

